Interpretation
Rare protein-altering variants in TERT, PARN, TERC, and RTEL1 are enriched in patients with IPF compared with controls, and, in the case of TERT, particularly in individuals without a risk allele at the rs35705950 locus. This suggests that multiple genetic factors contribute to sporadic IPF, which might implicate distinct mechanisms of pathogenesis and disease progression.
